22. The term “measures” encompasses a wide variety of legislative, executive, administrative and
other regulatory instruments, policies and practices, such as outreach or support programmes;
allocation and/or reallocation of resources; preferential treatment; targeted recruitment, hiring and promotion; numerical goals connected with time frames; and quota systems. The choice of a particular “measure” will depend on the context in which article 4, paragraph 1, is applied and on the specific goal it aims to achieve.
